    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> Log rotation is not provided with Logrus. Log rotation should be done by an external program (like `logrotate(8)`) that can compress and delete old log entries. It should not be a feature of the application-level logger.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sirupsen/logrus#rotation\r\nhttps://linux.die.net/man/8/logrotate\r\n\r\nPerhaps the action item here is to add documentation about how to use logrotate with Prysm, otherwise I think this feature request is a no-go for an application level implementation. While this may not be what you were looking for with this feature request, do you find that to be a reasonable resolution?\r\n\r\nWith regards to 11gb log file, did you have debug logging on? \r\nIt seems hard to imagine 11gb of logs without debug logging enabled. If this was at the info level or higher, then we really need to think about turning down the verbosity at info level. ",
