    "body": "Using logrotate would require prysm to reopen the logfile on a signal, else it will just keep writing to the moved logfile, ideally without restarting the processes. Using `copytruncate` with logrotate always comes with the risk of losing log messages.\r\n\r\nTrying with HUP, it just exits prysm. Maybe you could add listening to a signal to prysm (USR1?) which makes it reopen the logfile. \r\n",
